metadata.name: isometry II - watercolor #8
metadata.description:
This piece is a marriage of sorts. It begins with my "cityscape" interactive piece originally minted on Hic Et Nunc (here: https://teia.art/objkt/439560). This piece was used as the cover of The Tickle #30, and also received a static mint on Rarible. 

Several months later, I re-visited the land of isometrics and "fake 3D" for my "isometry" piece here on fx(hash), and which you can find here: https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/13199

I always wanted to do a true determinative piece in the style of the original "cityscapes," and this weekend I finally sat down and "ported" it to modern fx(hash) output. Since this piece and "isometry" share a commonality, I named this piece "isometry II," and added the "watercolor" as that was the original name of the piece before I minted it on H3N. 

I hope you enjoy it!

metadata.name: CA Panico #87
metadata.description:
Third chapter of the trilogy dedicated to Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.
 
Compared to CA Vista and CA Monti, CA Panico aims to further abstract the concept of landscape using CA rules in a more massive way.

The great variety of CA rules that controls the coloring and textures, noise influence, division into quadrants, chance of having glitches and outages all combined with 25 palettes and 5 different formats means that the outputs will be very varied and peculiar.

Press 'S' to download, you can zoom downloaded output to enjoy all the details.

metadata.name: Outdoor #13
metadata.description:
The moon/sun, sea, and background are created randomly by p5js, along with the infrastructure, and on top of it is an image drawn with Illustrator that incorporates angled lines.
The goal of this design is to display angular ideas placed on natural elements like the moon and sea in the simplest way possible.

metadata.name: Glass Arches #42
metadata.description:
Inspired by the art of stained glass, colored and patterned parts are arranged in a network of lead strips next to each other and act as shape-forming lines.
Their brilliant appearance is caused by the property of passing light through symmetrical pieces and asymmetric of different colors and refracting light from the center.

metadata.name: Endless #41
metadata.description:
There should be a miracle in painting.
For me, what matters most is the expression of simple and basic human feelings regarding fate, the past, the future, etc
It is my opinion that art should not reflect the feelings and statements of its creator.
As a result of my experience creating works, I have learned not to impose anything on the materials of my work, but rather to demonstrate the qualities and possibilities of them.
It doesn't take many things to see a work of art; it's attractive on its own. It is the rule of the game to repeat and expand, so the outputs in the final evaluation are conceptual.

metadata.name: Angular View #28
metadata.description:
The angle factor plays a significant role in determining how an image feels and looks.
When viewed from one angle, elements inside the frame might appear compressed and unclear, while when viewed from another angle, they might appear clear and distinct.
Choosing the right angle can encourage and guide the audience, while choosing the wrong angle can confuse and mislead him.
Therefore, when choosing the angle, one should consider aesthetic, technical, and emotional factors to present the subject to the viewer in the best light.
Depending on the angle, space and subject of the image are transformed and they can convey various meanings, including: logical visualization of space/impossible and free visualization, exaggeration and exaggeration/simplicity, stillness/movement, insider/alienation, mysterious/reliable, and complexity.
Made by p5.js

metadata.name: Angular Waves #49
metadata.description:
Changes in viewing angle can reveal or postpone story information, introduce a specific location or mood, or create visual variety.
In fact, every angle of view alters the mood, rhythm, and even the fictional events in the space.
With changes in the viewing angle, the image's emotional and visual characteristics change, and with those changes, the implicit meaning of the work changes as well.
Viewing angles are affected by the visual experiences of everyday life, which contribute to their semantic load.
In the same way, what a person learns from his surroundings is stored in his mind and used to understand and interpret an image.
Made by p5.js

The angles determine the audience's point of view in this way and by changing the angles, the audience can see the subject of the image from a new perspective.

metadata.name: Chromatic Chaos #32
metadata.description:
Chromatic Chaos is a vibrant and abstract generative artwork inspired by the colorful and expressive style of the renowned artist Wassily Kandinsky. The artwork is composed of a chaotic and dynamic arrangement of lines, stars, and geometric shapes, all rendered in a bright and energetic color palette. The lines and shapes seem to overlap and intersect, creating a sense of depth and movement within the composition. The overall effect is one of organized chaos, with each element vying for attention within the vibrant and playful composition. Through its use of color and form, Chromatic Chaos captures the essence of Kandinsky's bold and innovative style, inviting the viewer to explore and interpret its abstract and dynamic composition.



AI is a powerful tool that can perform complex calculations and analyze vast amounts of data much faster and more efficiently than humans. It can also recognize patterns and make predictions based on data, which can be incredibly valuable in a wide range of fields, from healthcare and finance to transportation and entertainment.

However, AI still lacks human-like creativity, empathy, and intuition. Humans are better at understanding context, emotions, and social dynamics, which are crucial in many situations. Combining AI with human intelligence can result in a powerful synergy that leverages the strengths of both. For example, AI can assist humans in making complex decisions or handling repetitive tasks, while humans can provide context and nuance to AI-generated insights.

Overall, the combination of AI and human intelligence has the potential to lead to groundbreaking discoveries and advancements across multiple fields, making it a cool and exciting prospect for the future.
